Preheat barbecue grill. Place parsley, garlic, and olive oil in small bowl of food processor or blender container. Cover; process until finely chopped. Spread pesto on beef steaks and bell peppers. Place steaks and peppers on grid over medium, ash-covered coals. Grill, uncovered, 14 to 16 minutes for medium rare to medium doneness and until peppers are tender, turning occasionally. Carve steaks. Season with salt and pepper. Serve with peppers.